      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_2",
      "text": "Individuals diagnosed with a germline heterozygous TP53 PV/LPV have LFS.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "case report",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:genetics:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_3",
      "text": "LFS is a hereditary cancer syndrome that is associated with increased risk for multiple cancers, including, but not limited to, breast cancer, sarcoma, central nervous system tumors, and adrenocortical carcinoma.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "case report",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:genetics:4:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_4",
      "text": "It has been determined that clonal hematopoiesis is causative of a blood/saliva next-generation sequencing result in 25%-38.8% of cases.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "case report",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:surgery:5:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "surgery_5",
      "text": "The breast cancer risk for women with LFS/germline TP53 LPVs/PVs is 80%-90%, with most breast cancers occurring at a younger age.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "case report",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
